# Tailwind CSS Usage

This project uses Tailwind CSS for styling. Follow these guidelines:

1. Use Tailwind utility classes directly in the JSX markup instead of creating separate CSS files when possible
2. Use the `@apply` directive in CSS files only when creating reusable component styles
3. Define custom colors and styles in `tailwind.config.js`
4. Use the provided color palette and spacing scales whenever possible
5. For responsive design, use Tailwind's built-in responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, and `2xl:`

Example of responsive design with Tailwind:
```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4">
  <div className="w-full md:w-1/2 p-4 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg">
    {/* Content */}
  </div>
  <div className="w-full md:w-1/2 p-4 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg">
    {/* Content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

Example of extending the theme in `tailwind.config.js`:
```js
/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
export default {
  content: [
    "./index.html",
    "./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}",
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        primary: {
          50: '#f0f9ff',
          100: '#e0f2fe',
          // ... other shades
          600: '#0284c7',
          700: '#0369a1',
        },
        secondary: {
          // ... custom secondary color shades
        },
      },
      fontFamily: {
        sans: ['Inter', 'sans-serif'],
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [],
}
```

